http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/NGO-rescues-boy/article14006433.ece

A six-year-old boy, who was allegedly thrashed by his mother following a tiff with her in-laws, was rescued by Childline NGO partner HELP on Monday.The boy, Siddavarapu Aaron, who sustained injuries, was rushed to Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Medical Sciences, Childline India Foundation district coordinator M. Kishore Kumar said.The District Child Welfare Committee (CWC) gave the custody of the boy to his grandmother and arranged for counselling for his mother, who had strained relationship with her husband and mother-in-law.